### **Accessible‑readability CSS**

```css
:root {
  --bg-main: #f5f7f8;
  --text-main: #222;
  --text-secondary: #555;
  --accent: #9ab;
  --link-color: #0645ad;
}

/* Global text and spacing */
body {
  background-color: var(--bg-main);
  color: var(--text-main);
  font-family: "Open Sans", "Lato", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
  font-size: 18px;               /* comfortable base size */
  line-height: 1.6;              /* spacious lines */
  letter-spacing: 0.02em;
}

/* Headings */
h2, h3 {
  color: var(--text-main);
  margin-top: 1.5em;
  margin-bottom: 0.5em;
  font-weight: 600;
}

/* Transcript blockquote */
blockquote {
  border-left: 4px solid var(--accent);
  padding-left: 1rem;
  background-color: #ffffff;
  font-size: 1.05em;
  margin: 1em 0;
}

/* Links */
a {
  color: var(--link-color);
  text-decoration: underline;
}

a:focus, a:hover {
  text-decoration-thickness: 3px; /* stronger indicator */
}

/* Resource list */
ul {
  list-style-type: disc;
  margin-left: 1.25rem;
}

/* Notes / disclaimers */
.note {
  font-size: 0.95rem;
  color: var(--text-secondary);
  margin-top: 1.5rem;
}

/* Responsive adjustments */
@media (max-width: 600px) {
  body { font-size: 16px; }
  blockquote { padding-left: 0.8rem; }
}
```

---

**Practical notes**

- The color choices maintain contrast ratios above 4.5 : 1 for WCAG AA compliance.  
- Fonts are sans‑serif for clarity; generous line height prevents crowding.  
- Responsive scaling down to 16 px on smaller screens keeps text digestible without zooming.  
- All interactive elements (links, focus states) show a clear visual change.

