### **Dark‑Mode & High‑Contrast Additions**

```css
/* Optional toggle button styles */
.theme-toggle {
  background:none;
  border:2px solid var(--accent);
  border-radius:4px;
  padding:0.4rem 0.8rem;
  margin:1rem 0;
  font-size:1rem;
  cursor:pointer;
}

/* Automatic dark mode for users who prefer it */
@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
  :root {
    --bg-main:#1e1f21;
    --text-main:#f1f1f1;
    --text-secondary:#c0c0c0;
    --accent:#7aa0ff;
    --link-color:#9ec6ff;
  }
  blockquote {
    background-color:#2a2b2e;
    border-left-color:var(--accent);
  }
}

/* High‑contrast mode for visitors who need it */
@media (prefers-contrast: more) {
  :root {
    --bg-main:#ffffff;
    --text-main:#000000;
    --text-secondary:#000000;
    --accent:#000000;
    --link-color:#0000ee;
  }
  a:focus, a:hover {
    outline:3px solid #000;
  }
}
```

**Usage**

- Include a small toggle button if you’d like users to switch themes manually, or rely on system preferences with `prefers-color-scheme`.  
- Test each scheme with online WCAG contrast checkers to confirm compliance.  
- Keep link and focus states distinct in all modes for keyboard navigation.

These styles complete a fully accessible page for your grounding resource, ensuring it’s easy to read no matter a visitor’s device, brightness setting, or visual needs.

